caption: Great place great old school mom and pop pizzeria. Family business that makes you feel like family. My kids favorite pizza spot in the summer..been eating pizza from them for the Las 20ss year's.. when you visit say Hi to Frank hes the Best.🙌🏼🙌🏼🙌🏼🙌🏼🙌🏼

It was my first visit to IVANA'S and Little Italy in The Bronx and I picked up one of their speciality heart shaped pepperoni pizzas IHO of Valentine's Day! The staff was so friendly and the pizza was warm and fresh. My kids absolutely loved it.  They have the heart shaped pizza available all of Feb for pick up.  Please support your local businesses!

We saw it when we arrived to the area and pledged to get some "to go" before we left.  And we did. and we are so glad we did. I got a LARGE meat calzone - which held up to the travel (didn't get soggy) and was simply deliciously seasoned.  I didn't know what I was getting with "meat" and it was a fine ground (beef?) in a chewy, crisp dough. We also got two enormous slices. AND....oh my! so glad we stopped (did I mention the Calzone are $3.50 and $5?!)
The food is ALWAYS fresh, hot and delicious!!! Been going there for years and the staff is friendly, inviting and accommodating. By far the best pizza around!!!❤️

I have been coming here since I was 9 years old. I hope this place stays open for the rest of my life. I told the manager to spell the name like my name. So back in the day it had two n's and I am so glad he took my lil self at my word and his word and changed the name for me. You can find old pics with the two n's but that I felt like was the first time anyone ever listened to what  I had to say. So when I walked by after we had the convo weeks later and it had changed I knew there was someone who heard me.
